LIBREVDEP(7)

# NAME

librevdep - reverse dependency auditing library

# DESCRIPTION

*librevdep* is a C++ library for auditing installed ELF objects and
reporting missing shared-library dependencies (DT_NEEDED entries that
cannot be resolved).

The library is designed to be embedded by higher-level tools such as
package managers and system auditors.
It is re-entrant and supports parallel execution through an explicit
context object and a thread-safe ELF cache.

The normative resolution contract is documented in
*revdep_semantics*(7).
These semantics are independent of execution mode
(serial or parallel).

# DESIGN OVERVIEW

*librevdep* is organized as a thin set of layers:

Configuration
	*revdep::RevdepConfig* defines global resolver directories and
	policy knobs.

Context
	*revdep::RevdepContext* owns configuration and shared state
	(notably the ELF cache).
	All mutable state is explicit and caller-controlled.

Engine
	Audit functions operate on files and packages and return
	structured findings.
	The library never prints by itself.

Parallel runner (optional)
	A helper that schedules many work items concurrently while
	keeping output deterministic when requested.

# THREADING

All audit entry points are re-entrant.

Parallel execution is supported by sharing one *revdep::ElfCache*
instance across threads.
The cache stores immutable ELF objects and is protected with a
read/write lock.

Do not mutate configuration while audits are running.

Caller-provided sinks must be thread-safe when invoked concurrently
(see *revdep_parallel*(3)).

# SEE ALSO

*revdep*(1),
*revdep.d*(5),
*revdep_semantics*(7)

